                  <msItem>
                     <p> 
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Ralph</forename> 
                           <surname>Bulge</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_109451">Purston</placeName>, jun.</persName>, 
               grants to <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename>, the abbot</persName>, and 
               <orgName key="org_109067">canons of St. Mary, Oseney</orgName>, in frankalmoigne, an annual rent of one penny, 
               which was accustomed to be paid to him by <persName>sir <forename>Jordan</forename>, the chaplain</persName>,
               for 2 messuages which he held of him in <placeName key="place_109268">Estrop</placeName>; also another rent of 1d., which 
               <persName>
                           <forename>Hugh</forename> de <surname>Lyons ("Leonibus")</surname>
                        </persName> and
               <persName nymRef="Lyons">
                           <forename>Matilda</forename> his wife</persName> were
               accustomed to pay for a messuage in the same village. 
                        (<origDate notBefore="1270" notAfter="1280" precision="low">c. 1270-80</origDate>.) 
                 
               </p>
